reviews.text:
This small shop has a very special type of Rice in Soup. Thirty to forty years ago, this type of Rice in Soup was very popular in small restaurants. As time goes by, they disappear in the menus. One reason might be because they could not be priced high so the restaurants are not interested to offer them. 
To make this Rice in Soup delicious, the restaurant has to prepare in advance a big volume of delicious soup as the basis of the dish. The customer when ordering this could choose two to three fresh food items like sliced beef, pork and fish. The restaurant would then simply boil these items in the soup and serves with some vegetable. The dish would be served in a big bowl with the delicious soup plus a bowl of steamed Rice. 
To enjoy this, the customer can either pour the steamed Rice into the big bowl and eat them mixed with soup. Or the other way is simply eat the steamed Rice and sip the soup after a few mouth. 
Man Hing Kee Restaurant (文興記) uses this Rice Soup as their specialty and uses very fresh and good quality meat to serve the customers. The soup is particular sweat with traditional taste. This Rice Soup is specially popular when the weather is hot when one has no appetite because of heat.

Eating there since I was a child. Simple dishes but rich of homemade taste. Especially love the veggie with pork and salty egg in soup and steam fish. Beef brisket rice or noodle are also very nice! Of course the deep flied fish ball with salty clam source are prefect too.
Great local style noodle place with lots of great dishes of dumplings, beef, pork nuckle
Good food at very reasonable prices
A very good price for money place, very local, homecook feel.

reviews.text:
One of the best place to go if you want to find cheap local food and street food hub. 

Away from the nowadays monopoly of shopping mall,  there are many small shops where the shop owners actually run the shop themselves which make the food more "alive". Varieties is great,  go any time and you would find something to eat.

Cash mostly.
Park sensibly on the street outside is ok.
Always crowded with people looking for snacks and food. It's really dirty and hot inside.
Numerous types of traditional fruits & foods.  Cheap price but good taste.
Many Hong Kong style snacks.  Cheap but delicious.
Amazing range of food stalls from desserts to satay skewers and noodles. All the food is affordable and delicious

這個所謂商場，仲衰過街市內裡悶熱，人多嘈雜如無必要免入。
筲箕湾太安楼商埸，它的楼齡超過30年，地下有很多不同種類啇店，行人通道非常窄，很多啇户擺放貨物，在行人通道二旁。萬一發生火警，後果很難想像。這是本人意見。
晚上下班一族人流集中宵夜小食旺點。空調抽風不足

不應叫商埸，叫平民走廊。
這裡唯一好處是平價街邊小食多，如果不講求買相，味道等... 是可接受的。
